Search Results Example

The border is defined on the sidebar element. Because the blocks have display: table-cell the sidebar is always as tall as the containing div, and the border always stretches the full height.

This page demonstrates search results as generated by ls. The structure of the search results is designed so that the item title is "encountered" before the checkbox. 

<div class="row result">
    <h4>The wombat : common wombats in Australia...</h4>
    <div class="span1 select">
        <label><input type="checkbox" /><span class="offscreen">Select item 1</span></label>
    </div>
    <div class="span11 push-1">
        <div class="result-metadata-author">
            by Triggs, Barbara.
        </div>
        <div class="result-metadata-published">
            Published 1988
        </div>
        <div class="result-access-link">
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <a href="/Record/005655916" class="cataloglinkhref">Catalog Record</a>
                </li>

                <li>
                    <a href="http://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=coo.31924052400748;q1=wombat" class="limited-access">Limited (search-only)</a>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

Note in the examples below that link icons are presented using CSS icon fonts.
